column5:
Merge pull request #78 from jensutbult/master

Added support for Xcode 7.3

Merge pull request #73 from Nekrich/master

Xcode 7.2 Support
Prevent state persistence so debugging doesn't open the Polychromatic project up again
Prevent flickering when first opening a document by checking if the nodeType is going to be changed.
Treat warnings as errors, make the build settings more strict, fix a minor error that was generated in swizzling
Remove PLYVariableManager class and replace it with functions
Clean up prefixes and methods in the preferences category
Clean up the highlighting hook category
Comment out the data injection category
Make the PLYDataInjection class not use stringly-typed arguments >_<
Extract first-run logic into its own class.

Merge pull request #72 from ShingoFukuyama/master

Add UUID for Xcode 7.1

Merge pull request #71 from ShingoFukuyama/master

Fixed for Xcode 7.0.1 El Capitan
Project update, silence warnings in class-dump headers.
Launch the GM now on debug.
Use +load instead of initialize with a dispatch_once, which is awful.
Re-format, fix an error passing in and remove some mutability
Use a folder reference for themes so it's easy to add them later, sort all the top level items in the file browser

Merge pull request #69 from jklausa/patch-1

Add Xcode 7 GM UUID.
Fix highlighting failure in Swift due to re-assigning pointer (fixes #49)

Merge pull request #59 from rolandleth/variable-coloring-for-swift

self.property coloring for Swift.
Bump version of Xcode built with to Xcode 7-b5.

Merge pull request #67 from richardjrossiii/fix-xcode-crash

Fix crash on Xcode 7 beta related to bad casting of IMP types.
Fix crash on Xcode 7 beta related to bad casting of IMP types.

Merge pull request #66 from ealeksandrov/master

Added Xcode 6.4 UUID
Remove duplicate Xcode UDID from 6.2 or whatever.

Merge pull request #61 from otaran/xcode-6.3.2-compatibility

Add Xcode 6.3.2 compatibility UUID

Variable coloring for Swift.

Added `nodeType == 16` check

Merge pull request #55 from drozycki/compatibilityFix

Add compatibility strings for XCode 6.2 and 6.3
Remove requirement for workspace and its index. Also check for a string before requesting a var color.
Now colors property names in @properties and prevents setter/getter attributes from receiving coloring. Fixes #17.
Add method for determining inheritance of a node
Micro-optimizations to save time as well as fixing the coloration of absolutely everything.
Use the production Xcode version again.
Switched hash from NSString-hash to Fowler–Noll–Vo hash (@McZonk found this hash)
Update the scheme to make it build and run properly. Fixes #35.

Merge pull request #44 from kolinkrewinkel/xcode-5-note

Polish up the readme, including a note about Xcode 5 compatibility.
Polish up the readme, including a note about Xcode 5 compatibility. Closes #13.

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/mccannmax/Polychromatic into mccannmax-master

Conflicts:
	Polychromatic.xcodeproj/project.xcworkspace/xcshareddata/Polychromatic.xccheckout

Merge pull request #42 from zenangst/master

Add Compatibility UUID

Merge pull request #36 from neonichu/master

Added Xcode 6 GM Compatibility UUID.
Add a gitignore and clean out Xcode's shit.

Merge pull request #22 from kolinkrewinkel/polychromatic-v1.0.1

Polychromatic v1.0.1.
Merge 0xced branch. Not sure what just happened with git.
Code style fix for theme directory stuff.

Create the themes directory before installing them

[Fixes] https://github.com/kolinkrewinkel/Polychromatic/issues/19
quick fix for issue #14, this prevents just the crash and does not solve the origin of the bug

Use DEVELOPER_DIR instead of SYSTEM_APPS_DIR

This fixes compilation if Xcode was renamed.

Merge pull request #9 from ayanonagon/master

Small typo fix in Readme.

Merge pull request #8 from a2/patch-1

Remove extraneous whitespace in preference pane.
Move files out of the main directory.

Merge pull request #5 from kolinkrewinkel/fix-colorwell-enabled-state

Enable/disable colour wells appropriately

Merge pull request #3 from kolinkrewinkel/samples

Sample Themes
Finish adding copying functionality on first-run and add menu item.
Remove references to BBUIndexHelper-It didn't end up being of use anyways. Also clean up some random code.
Add 'Carbon' as a starting bundled theme.

Merge pull request #2 from kolinkrewinkel/literacy

Literacy: All those settings need to be read and understood
Return colors that the theme intends to provide.
Attach the brightness and saturation to the actual data values.

Merge pull request #1 from kolinkrewinkel/injection

Injection: Preferences by way of swizzling
Fix text blurriness issues by removing -setDrawsBackground:NO.
Fix some bizarre layout issues courtesy of scroll view stupidity.
Success. Adjustable color wells. And they revert back to how they're supposed to be, too
Add another slider, and begin iteration to meddle with the color wells.
One slider down and some flipped coords later~
Change tableview style to match that of the default (with source list highlight but a white background.)
Table views are fun. On iOS.
Positioning is fixed. No one knows why.

Set autoresizingMask on inserted view, and fix up in-document constraints

Using `translatesAutoresizingMaskIntoConstraints` means that we avoid
having to wrestle with auto layout.
Begin the layer visualization and working towards a preferences view. To sketches...
Well this works to change the view controller. Still whines in console but seemingly to no averse affect.
It's complaining in the consol about something to do with registering objects and stateTokens, but we're getting somewhere now.
...I mean, it's loading the other view. But it's crappy.
Should be actually replacing it now.
Properly replace the view controller and not crash.
Hide the normal font and whatnot view.
Work on injecting items into the preferences view.
Clean out old variables on reindex.
Decrease the amount of colors flying around.
Remove coloring of method signatures in favor of only the arguments.
Add comment coloring and revise the gray tones of the other meta stuff.
Add system class coloring and do some more progress on colorizing things.
Begin the work start colorizing things step by step.
On the back of the system, now we're parsing. Maybe not the best way (it should probably be us that decided the boundaries by way of recursion), but it's a start.
Add a little bit of an explanation.
Interesting progress: ranges are simply manipulated within the method. So you take an index and run with it as far as possible, then leave it up to Xcode to call you back with the reaminder.
